      "set:html": "<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Create a <code dir=\"auto\">Timer</code> object and call <code dir=\"auto\">begin()</code> <strong>before using the elapsed classes</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>For each task you want to time, create a separate <code dir=\"auto\">elapsedMicros</code>, <code dir=\"auto\">elapsedMillis</code>, or <code dir=\"auto\">elapsedSeconds</code> object, depending on the required precision.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>In your main loop, check if the elapsed time exceeds your threshold<br>\n(for example, <code dir=\"auto\">if (emillis >= 1000)</code>).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>If the condition is met, perform the task and <strong>reset the counter</strong> by assigning zero (<code dir=\"auto\">emillis = 0;</code>).</p>\n</li>\n</ol>"
